{{refimprove|date=January 2015}}
'''Dar al-Bashair''' is a royal palace located in the Bir al-Azab district of [[Sana'a]], Yemen.

It was the residence of King [[Muhammad al-Badr]]. On September 26, 1962, the commander of the royal guard [[Abdullah al-Sallal]] in an act of state [[treason]] staged a coup and had the palace [[Shell (projectile)|shelled]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/obituary-imam-muhammad-albadr-1309697.html|title=Obituary: Imam Muhammad al-Badr|work=The Independent}}</ref>

