'''Mokole''' (or ''Mokollé, Mokwale, Monkole, Féri'') is a [[Yoruba languages|Yoruba]] language spoken in the villages surrounding the town of [[Kandi, Benin|Kandi]] in [[Benin]]. It's the northernmost variety of Yoruba.

