The '''Shahsevan''' ({{lang-az|Şahsevənlər}}), are a branch of the Turkic Oghuz groups,<ref name="Shahsevan-2">{{Cite book| editor= Yaşar Kalafat| title= Balkanlar'dan Uluğ Türkistan'a Türk halk inançları |edition=Kültür Bakanlığı| year=2002|volume=2 |page= 386}}</ref> sub-ethnic group of [[Azerbaijani people]], located primarily in [[Iran]] and on the territory of the present-day [[Azerbaijan|Republic of Azerbaijan]].<ref name="Shahsevan-3">{{Cite book| editor= A.Z. Abdullaiev | title= Türk dillerinin tarihsel gelişme sorunları |edition=Atatürk Kültür, Dil, ve Tarih Yüksek Kurumu| year=1996 |page= 66}}</ref> The name ''Shahsevan'' means "adherents of the Shah".

